<TITLE>Naveen rejects Negotiation committee on Mahanadi river, calls for early formation of Tribunal to resolve the dispute</TITLE>


<TEXT>
The Mahanadi water dispute involving Odisha and Chhatisgarh was further <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">complicated</EVENT> with Odisha Chief Minister Naveen Patnaik demanding <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE">setting</EVENT> up of Water Tribunal while <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">rejecting</EVENT> the <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">constitution</EVENT> of a Negotiation Committee by the Union Water Resource Minister to <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE">resolve</EVENT> the issue. <EVENT eid="e6" class="STATE">Expressing</EVENT> his strong reservation over the formation of Negotiation Committee, Mr.Patnaik in a letter to Prime Minister Narendra Modi <EVENT eid="e7" class="REPORTING">said</EVENT> such a committee will only <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE">delay</EVENT> the formation of water Tribunal and <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">allow</EVENT> the Chhatisgarh government to <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">complete</EVENT> all the ongoing projects over the upper end of Mahanadi river, which the state government has been vociferously <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">objecting</EVENT> as it would have serious effect on the livelihood of missions of people in the state solely depending upon the Mahanadi river, considered as a life line for Odisha. The Chief Minister <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">urged</EVENT> the Prime Minister to <EVENT eid="e13" class="OCCURRENCE">direct</EVENT> the Union Water Resource Ministry to <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE">withdraw</EVENT> the office memorandum on the <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE">constitution</EVENT> of the Negotiation Committee and <EVENT eid="e16" class="I_ACTION">initiate</EVENT> constitution of Tribunal <EVENT eid="e17" class="OCCURRENCE">stating</EVENT> that the water <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE">dispute</EVENT> on Mahanadi <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">raised</EVENT> by his government cannot be <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">resolved</EVENT> by the <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE">negotiation</EVENT>. Mr.Patnaik also <EVENT eid="e22" class="I_ACTION">urged</EVENT> the Prime Minister to <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE">direct</EVENT> the Chhatisgarh government to <EVENT eid="e24" class="OCCURRENCE">stop</EVENT> all the ongoing construction work on Mahanadi forthwith and <EVENT eid="e25" class="REPORTING">expressed</EVENT> his opinion <EVENT eid="e26" class="OCCURRENCE">stating</EVENT> that " I am open to a <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE">meeting</EVENT> at your level as a last and final chance to <EVENT eid="e28" class="OCCURRENCE">settle</EVENT> the <EVENT eid="e29" class="OCCURRENCE">dispute</EVENT> by negotiation if the <EVENT eid="e30" class="OCCURRENCE">meeting</EVENT> of chief ministers of the riparian states is <EVENT eid="e31" class="OCCURRENCE">called</EVENT> immediately. The Chief Minister also <EVENT eid="e32" class="OCCURRENCE">expressed</EVENT> his deep concern as the central government has <EVENT eid="e33" class="OCCURRENCE">failed</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e34" class="I_ACTION">instruct</EVENT> the Chhatisgarh government to <EVENT eid="e35" class="OCCURRENCE">stop</EVENT> the construction work in respect of ongoing projects <EVENT eid="e36" class="OCCURRENCE">started</EVENT> unilaterally in the Mahanadi basis as repeatedly <EVENT eid="e37" class="OCCURRENCE">raised</EVENT> by his government which has <EVENT eid="e38" class="OCCURRENCE">caused</EVENT> serious discontentment in the minds of the people of the state who are hugely dependent on the water of Mahanadi river. Mr.Patnaik also <EVENT eid="e39" class="REPORTING">stated</EVENT> that the <EVENT eid="e40" class="OCCURRENCE">constitution</EVENT> of the Negotiation Committee is not in accordance with the provisions of the Inter State River Water Dispute Act <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="1956">1956</TIMEX3> which <EVENT eid="e41" class="OCCURRENCE">puts</EVENT> the responsibility on the centre to <EVENT eid="e42" class="OCCURRENCE">negotiate</EVENT> after <EVENT eid="e43" class="OCCURRENCE">receiving</EVENT> the complaint and in this regard the the principle of federal relations <EVENT eid="e44" class="OCCURRENCE">mandates</EVENT> that the constitutional functionaries namely the Prime Minister or Union Minister for Water Resources should <EVENT eid="e45" class="OCCURRENCE">conduct</EVENT> the negotiation with the Chief Ministers of riparian states rather than appointi8ng a committee headed by an officer of the sub ordinate office such as the Central Water Commission. UNI DP KK
</TEXT>


